  "text": "Vibrio cholerae sialidase (EC 3.2.1.18), cholera toxin, and its B subunit were obtained from Calbiochem-Behring Corp. (La Jolla, CA). NalO4 and KBI-L were obtained from Sigma Chemical Co. (St. Louis, MO). KBal-h (68 Ci/ mmol) was purchased from Research Products International Corp. (Mt. Prospect, IL). Fluoreseein-and rhodamine-labeled rabbit anti-goat IgG were obtained through Miles Laboratories, Inc. (Naperville, 1L). Cholera toxin was iodinated as described previously [CITATION_1] . Affinity-purified goat anti-chicken cellular fibronectin antibodies were prepared as described by Yamada (37) . The 70,000-mol-wt, amino-terminal fragment of fibronectin was prepared as described by McKeown-Longo and Mosher (24).",
